<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Song_Dynasty&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<p><cite id="cnote_a"><a href="#ref_a" title=""><b>^</b></a></cite>&#160;<b>a:</b>&#160;During the reign of the Song Dynasty the world population grew from about 250 million to approximately 330 million, a difference of 80 million. Please also see <a href="/wiki/Medieval_demography" title="Medieval demography">Medieval demography</a>.<br />
<cite id="cnote_b"><a href="#ref_b" title=""><b>^</b></a></cite>&#160;<b>b:</b>&#160;For the history of paper-printed money, please see <a href="/wiki/Banknote" title="Banknote">banknote</a>.<br />
<cite id="cnote_c"><a href="#ref_c" title=""><b>^</b></a></cite>&#160;<b>c:</b>&#160;Despite the establishment of permanent standing navy in Song Dynasty, China already had a long naval history prior to the Song, see <a href="/wiki/Naval_history_of_China" title="Naval history of China">Naval history of China</a>.<br />
<cite id="cnote_d"><a href="#ref_d" title=""><b>^</b></a></cite>&#160;<b>d:</b>&#160;As opposed to the previous <a href="/wiki/Han_Dynasty" title="Han Dynasty">Han</a> and <a href="/wiki/Tang_Dynasty" title="Tang Dynasty">Tang Dynasty</a>, each of which boasted roughly 50 million inhabitants<br />
<cite id="cnote_e"><a href="#ref_e" title=""><b>^</b></a></cite>&#160;<b>e:</b>&#160;See the <a href="/wiki/Song_Dynasty#Technology" title="Song Dynasty">technology</a> section for more information.<br /></p>
